# Beef mince pasta


A nice classic italian dish that is easy to cook and can be paired with a variety of cheeses, You will need
a saucepan, pot, stainer and cooking spoon:

- ‚è≤Ô∏è Prep time: 1 min
- üç≥ Cook time: 20 min
- üçΩÔ∏è Servings: 4-6

## Ingredients

- Garlic
- Thyme
- Basil
- Rosemary
- Salt
- Pepper
- Parmisan cheese (optional)
- Paprika (optional)
- 350g Dried Pasta
- 2tbs Oil or Animal fat
- 2 Cups Passata
- 1kg Beef mince

## Directions

1. Bring a pan to the stove and add oil of your choice
2. Cook the mince on the saucepan, using your spoon to chop the chunks until it is all browned
3. Bring a pot filled with water to the stove on high while your cooking the mince
4. Once the mince is browned add the passata. (If its storebought, wash the jar into the pan with water)
5. Add the spices (Garlic, thyme, basil, rosemary, salt, pepper and paprika)
6. Set the stove on low and stir until the sauce is thickened (Give the sauce a taste to check quality)
7. Once the pot is boiled add the 350g pasta packet and stir to prevent sticking
8. Once the pasta has enough slack to freely boil, leave for 8-11 minutes
9. Check the pasta by tasting a strand to your liking
10. Once ready, strain the pasta then transfer back into the pot and add the mince sauce
11. Serve yourself and sprinkle some cheese on top then enjoy!
